s%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67d48bf9585f1dff88b23f14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-trump-bump-selloff-correction-outlook-prediction-investing-strategy-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Stocks%20are%20off%20to%20a%20shaky%20start%20in%20Trump's%20second%20term%2C%20but%20bullish%20strategists%20aren't%20losing%20hope.%20Here's%20where%20they're%20investing%20after%20a%20correction.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jfaris%40businessinsider.com%20(James%20Faris)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A25%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstock-market-trump-bump-selloff-correction-outlook-prediction-investing-strategy-2025-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20A%20Columbia%20Student%20Escaped%20From%20US%20Amid%20Immigration%20Crackdown%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ERanjani%20Srinivasan%2C%20a%2037-year-old%20Indian%20student%20pursuing%20a%20doctoral%20degree%20in%20urban%20planning%20at%20Columbia%20University%2C%20was%20forced%20to%20flee%20the%20United%20States%20after%20her%20student%20visa%20was%20revoked.%20The%20US%20Department%20of%20State%20canceled%20her%20visa%20on%20March%205%2C%20citing%20security%20concerns%20related%20to%20her%20alleged%20involvement%20in%20activities%20supporting%20Hamas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESrinivasan's%20troubles%20began%20when%20she%20became%20entangled%20in%20the%20government's%20crackdown%20on%20pro-Palestinian%20protests.%20Despite%20no%20evidence%20being%20provided%2C%20she%20was%20accused%20of%20supporting%20violence%20and%20links%20to%20Hamas.%20The%20situation%20escalated%20when%20federal%20immigration%20agents%20arrived%20at%20her%20apartment%2C%20prompting%20her%20to%20make%20a%20swift%20decision%20to%20leave%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20The%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20Srinivasan%20expressed%20her%20fear%20and%20uncertainty%2C%20stating%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20atmosphere%20seemed%